{"type":"HOSTEL","name":"Noah's Ark Backpackers","nameEN":"Noah's Ark Backpackers","isActive":true,"isNew":false,"description":"Nestled in a beautifully Heritage NZ building that used to be a presbytery, our hostel offers a unique blend of historic charm and it is located just a short walk from Greymouth city centre & railway station. \n\nWe provide a welcoming and affordable stay for travellers exploring the stunning West Coast. Whether you're here for adventure or relaxation, enjoy our cozy accommodations, friendly atmosphere, and easy access to local attractions.\n\nStay with us and experience the best of Greymouthâ€™s heritage and hospitality! We provide warm, friendly and welcoming quality budget accommodation just about 250m from Greymouth town centre!\n\nWhile enjoying your stay at Noah's Ark you can take in the west coast sunset from our balcony,  or have a barbeque and then laze in the hammock in our large garden. To explore the area we have two bikes that are free to use for you and you can give the new coastal cycle way a go! Or we can direct you to the local bush walks and nearby beaches or advise you about the various adventure activities.  \n\nUnlimited free Wi-Fi - so it's easy to stay in touch with family and friends or plan your trip ahead.\n\nNoah's Ark offers characterful spacious private and shared rooms that are warm and comfortable, with self-controlled heaters, clean linen, duvets and spare blankets. The rooms are beautifully decorated with fun animal themes like tigers, penguins, leopards and more.\n\nFrom May to September our WINTER DEALS are on! If you are enjoying the cosy atmosphere we're making it easier to stay longer by giving you an additional night free if you book 3 or more nights! (Conditions apply).\n\nThere is a log fire and a new big heat pump that keep things warm on cooler days. Also, book swap and lots of games. There is a separate TV room with new Samsung Smart TV and comfy sofas.\n\nWe pride ourselves on providing clean bat